{"title": "Who Can Create Drug Recipes?", "body": "Who Can Create Drug Recipes?\n  As detailed in Drug Recipes Defined, drug recipes are customised combinations you can create and prescribe in MediRecords.\n\n\n\nDrug Recipes can only be created by those who have access to the feature and its functions. This is largely determined by Subscription plan settings - only users with Clinical or Integrated plans are able to access this.\nTo check your subscription, click on the Person Icon and select Profile.\n\n\n\nClick on Subscription.\nThis will show you your subscription plan.\n\n\nFor urgent assistance, please contact MediRecords support on 1300 103 903 during business hours."}